<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="136" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Cephalon with well developed quadrangular lateral lobes; male uropod exopodites elongated and pereopod VII ischium with setose areas on rostral surface and ventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="136" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,223,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[353,411,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Body</emphasis>
flattened; length up to 
<quantity box="[681,762,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
in both males and females. Color pale brown to dark gray with usual muscles spots (
<figureCitation box="[458,544,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1505,1527]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,325,1459]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,318,1466]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. A, living specimens of Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov. from the type locality; B, holotype; C, a female paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847411/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig 2A</figureCitation>
–C). 
<emphasis box="[601,662,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Head</emphasis>
with well developed quadrangular lateral lobes; median lobe with incision in middle; vertex granulated with several pointed tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[994,1069,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,206,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1416,197,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, head and first pereonite; B, antenna; C, telson and uropods; D, pereopod I; E, pereopod VII; F, pereopod VII ischium, frontal view; G, pereopod VII ischium, caudal view. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847413/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A). 
<emphasis box="[1120,1214,296,319]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Antenna</emphasis>
long and slender, surpassing posterior margin of pereon-tergite II; fifth article of peduncle longer than flagellum, with length: width ratio 10:1; flagellum with two articles, proximal one three times as long as distal one (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1182,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,206,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1416,197,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, head and first pereonite; B, antenna; C, telson and uropods; D, pereopod I; E, pereopod VII; F, pereopod VII ischium, frontal view; G, pereopod VII ischium, caudal view. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847413/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis box="[199,279,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Pereon</emphasis>
granulated with conspicuous pointed tubercles. Pereonite I with concave posterolateral margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,206,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1416,197,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, head and first pereonite; B, antenna; C, telson and uropods; D, pereopod I; E, pereopod VII; F, pereopod VII ischium, frontal view; G, pereopod VII ischium, caudal view. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847413/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis box="[199,325,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Pereopod I</emphasis>
ischium triangular, carpus with depression on rostral surface equipped with slender scales (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,206,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1416,197,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, head and first pereonite; B, antenna; C, telson and uropods; D, pereopod I; E, pereopod VII; F, pereopod VII ischium, frontal view; G, pereopod VII ischium, caudal view. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847413/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis box="[199,265,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Pleon</emphasis>
with continuous outline with pereon, granulated with tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[983,1049,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,206,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1416,197,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, head and first pereonite; B, antenna; C, telson and uropods; D, pereopod I; E, pereopod VII; F, pereopod VII ischium, frontal view; G, pereopod VII ischium, caudal view. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847413/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
E). 
<emphasis box="[1088,1157,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Telson</emphasis>
triangular, with concave sides and acute apex, not surpassing uropod-protopodites. 
<emphasis box="[819,905,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Uropod</emphasis>
exopodites as long as telson in females, up to three times as long as telson in males (
<figureCitation box="[590,657,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,206,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1416,197,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, head and first pereonite; B, antenna; C, telson and uropods; D, pereopod I; E, pereopod VII; F, pereopod VII ischium, frontal view; G, pereopod VII ischium, caudal view. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847413/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C). 
<emphasis box="[700,794,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Pleopod</emphasis>
exopodites I–II with monospiracular internal lungs (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,445,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[172,1412,435,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, pleopod endopodite I; B, pleopod exopodite I; C, pleopod II; D, pleopod exopodite III; E, pleopod exopodite IV; F, pleopod exopodite V. Scales = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847415/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
B–C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
Male: 
<emphasis box="[275,446,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Pereopods I–II</emphasis>
merus and carpus with brushes of setae. 
<emphasis box="[932,1086,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Pereopod VII</emphasis>
ischium with concave ventral margin equipped with hairy brush of small setae, rostral surface with setose area (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1150,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1626,1648]" captionTargetBox="[186,1416,206,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1416,197,1610]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, head and first pereonite; B, antenna; C, telson and uropods; D, pereopod I; E, pereopod VII; F, pereopod VII ischium, frontal view; G, pereopod VII ischium, caudal view. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847413/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
E). 
<emphasis box="[1192,1285,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Pleopod</emphasis>
endopodite I straight, apex with line of short setae (
<figureCitation box="[577,644,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,445,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[172,1412,435,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, pleopod endopodite I; B, pleopod exopodite I; C, pleopod II; D, pleopod exopodite III; E, pleopod exopodite IV; F, pleopod exopodite V. Scales = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847415/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A); exopodite I with short rounded hind lobe, outer margin with row of small setae (
<figureCitation box="[293,363,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,445,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[172,1412,435,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, pleopod endopodite I; B, pleopod exopodite I; C, pleopod II; D, pleopod exopodite III; E, pleopod exopodite IV; F, pleopod exopodite V. Scales = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847415/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
B). Pleopod endopodite II as long as exopodite; exopodite triangular with line of seta on outer margin (
<figureCitation box="[246,316,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,445,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[172,1412,435,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, pleopod endopodite I; B, pleopod exopodite I; C, pleopod II; D, pleopod exopodite III; E, pleopod exopodite IV; F, pleopod exopodite V. Scales = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847415/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C). Pleopod exopodites III–IV with concave outer margins (
<figureCitation box="[995,1062,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,445,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[172,1412,435,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, pleopod endopodite I; B, pleopod exopodite I; C, pleopod II; D, pleopod exopodite III; E, pleopod exopodite IV; F, pleopod exopodite V. Scales = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847415/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
D–E) bearing line of small setae. Pleopod exopodite V triangular with line of seta on outer margin (
<figureCitation box="[890,958,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[180,1409,445,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[172,1412,435,1967]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Porcellio mehrdadi sp. nov., male, paratype. A, pleopod endopodite I; B, pleopod exopodite I; C, pleopod II; D, pleopod exopodite III; E, pleopod exopodite IV; F, pleopod exopodite V. Scales = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/847415/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="136" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,908,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kashani &amp; Ahdiyeh &amp; Zahra, 2017" authorityName="Kashani &amp; Ahdiyeh &amp; Zahra" authorityYear="2017" box="[321,537,908,933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mehrdadi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,537,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Porcellio mehrdadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[544,634,908,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[544,634,908,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is characterized by the well developed quadrangular lateral lobes of the head; male pereopod VII ischium with the setose areas on rostral surface and ventral margin, and elongated uropod exopodites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<bibRefCitation author="Schmalfuss" box="[199,412,1015,1040]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" refString="Schmalfuss, H. (1992) The terrestrial isopod genus Porcellio in western Asia (Oniscidea: Porcellionidae). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A, 475, 1 - 45." type="journal article" year="1992">Schmalfuss (1992)</bibRefCitation>
revised the western Asian species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[852,955,1015,1040]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[852,955,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Porcellio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Schmalfuss" authorityYear="2003" box="[1074,1176,1017,1040]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis box="[1074,1176,1017,1040]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">P. evansi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1885" box="[1236,1372,1015,1040]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoletus">
<emphasis box="[1236,1372,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">P. obsoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[312,361,1053,1076]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Geographically, the new species is distributed within the distributional range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Schmalfuss" authorityYear="2003" box="[1267,1365,1053,1076]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellionidae" genus="Porcellio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evansi">
<emphasis box="[1267,1365,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">P. evansi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it was found even syntopically with the latter species in one locality. The two species, however, differ in their coloration, in the shape of the head and telson and in possessing the setose areas on pereopod VII ischium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1318,1159,1184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" box="[199,1318,1159,1184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Mehrdad Rezaei who collected the species for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,571,1196,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,1221]" box="[199,571,1196,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1196,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[518,567,1197,1220]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="136">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
